This paper is about personalizing dialogue agents, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Specifically, the paper focuses on improving chit-chat models by conditioning on profile information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and speech processing. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as training models, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper aims to improve the engagement of dialogue agents, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves collecting and analyzing data, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the resulting dialogue, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
